  "blurb": "A contemporary-Thai clifftop villa on Phuket's northwest coast, perched above Layan with the Andaman Sea filling every window. Five bedrooms over two levels, a 12.5-metre infinity pool, a games room and a private chef — built for big families and long, sunset-soaked weeks.",
  "detail": "Set on an exclusive estate above Phuket's quiet northwest coast, this contemporary-Thai residence rises across two clifftop levels, framed on every side by forest green and the open Andaman. The upper floor opens into a soaring formal living room — high ceilings, polished hardwood and three sliding-glass walls that pull the view straight in — leading out to a wraparound balcony made for sundowners, and a twelve-seat dining room where your private chef sends out Thai, Western and Asian menus to order.\n\nDownstairs, the formality gives way to calm: a shaded living sala, alfresco dining under the breeze, and a 12.5-metre infinity pool that runs to the edge of the greenery. A games room with a snooker table, two lounge areas and Apple TV keeps every generation happy. Of the five bedrooms, the upper-floor master takes the view through full-height windows; the rest open straight to the pool, with one turned over to the children as a four-bunk dorm.\n\nThe home comes fully staffed — a villa manager, private chef, daily housekeeping, gardener and security — with Trisara and Banana Beach just minutes down the headland. Tell us your dates and we'll arrange transfers, provisioning, and anything else the week calls for.",
